activeDisbursementID.descr: the id of the currently active disbursement

activeDisbursementWindow.descr: the unix timestamp signifying the start of the current disbursement

akitaDAO.descr: the app ID of the Akita DAO

allowLateSignups.descr: whether signups are allowed after the staking pool begins

creator.descr: the address of the creator of the staking pool

disbursementCursor.descr: the cursor for the current disbursement

disbursementPhase.descr: a sub status of the disbursement phase of the pool

endTimestamp.descr: the timestamp when the pool ends

entryID.descr: the number of entries in a pool

gateID.descr: the gate id of the pool

gateSize.descr: the size of the gate were using

lastDisbursementTimestamp.descr: the round the last reward was last paid out on

marketplace.descr: marketplace is pool creation side marketplace

maxEntries.descr: the maximum entries allowed for the pool

qualifiedStake.descr: the total qualified stake for the pool

qualifiedStakers.descr: the count of qualified stake during the preparation phase of a disbursement

raffleCursor.descr: winning ticket cursor for tracking the current position in winning tickets

reward.descr: the reward asset for the pool

rewardInterval.descr: the interval that rewards should be paid out on in seconds

signupTimestamp.descr: the timestamp when sign ups for the pool are allowed

stakeKey.descr:
the name for the meta merkle asset group to validate staking
stake key can be empty if distribution !== DistributionTypePercentage

startTimestamp.descr: the timestamp when the pool starts

status.descr: the status the pool is in

totalStaked.descr: the total amount staked in the pool

type.descr: the method of staking to be used for the pool

version.descr: the current version of the contract

vrfGetFailureCount.descr: counter for how many times we've failed to get rng from the beacon

winningTickets.descr: the winning numbers for a raffle disbursement pool

returns.desc: a boolean of whether sign ups are open
a boolean of whether the pool is live

args.name: asset
args.desc: The asset to be opted into

methods.desc: optin tells the contract to opt into an asa

returns.desc: the mbr created for each boxmap entry
